data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","content_index":0,"item_id":"msg_08db62c507829c5a006a0fcaad74f481999c776cbbbc49202f","logprobs":[],"output_index":1,"sequence_number":111,"text":"ABRACADABRA\nHere's a simple iterative Python function to calculate a factorial:\n\ndef factorial(n):\n    if not isinstance(n, int):\n        raise TypeError(\"n must be a non-negative integer\")\n    if n < 0:\n        raise ValueError(\"n must be a non-negative integer\")\n    result = 1\n    for i in range(2, n + 1):\n        result *= i\n    return result\n\nIf you prefer a recursive version, I can provide that as well."}

